Product name: Napier Necklace and Earrings Miami Collection 1992
Description:
Napier Necklace and Earrings Large and Colorful
Large and colorful is really an understatement. This is from the 1992 "Miami" collection by Napier.
It is documented on page 683 of the book "The Napier Co.,Defining 20th Century American Costume Jewelry" by Melinda L. Lewis with Henry Swen. 
The medallion of this necklace measures 3" in diameter and the pierced earrings measure 1 5/8" in diameter. The bright colors of blue, green and pink are practically neon as light hits them. The necklace chain is 30" long. This is definitely costume jewelry that makes a big statement. All three pieces are signed Napier and they are all in excellent condition. This set is not only large and colorful but is a very collectible set of Napier.

Description:
The "No Fuss Calligraphy Starter Kit" (Includes calligraphy pen)
Written, and featuring calligraphy by Ashley Gardner of Printable Wisdom
I remember when I first decided to learn calligraphy. I bought a fancy book that promised to teach me the art of this beautiful style of writing. I waited for days for the book to be delivered and was so excited to open it up and start creating fun quotes and writing song lyrics (let‚Äôs be honest, so I  could post them on my website for my friends to ooh and aah over). But, the first page directed me to a list of fifteen different supplies I‚Äôd have to buy... just to get started! Then, I had to do daily drills of circles and loops before I could even write my first letter.
Being very impatient, I thought there had to be a quicker way to start  creating beautiful calligraphy. From my impatience, the ‚ÄúNo Fuss Calligraphy‚Äù Starter Kit was born! There‚Äôs no shopping list, no drills, just a few simple pointers to get you started on the right foot in the wonderful world of calligraphy.
If you want to learn stilted and rigid lettering, this kit isn‚Äôt for you. This is for the free spirit who wants to develop their own style. I often get asked, ‚ÄúHow can I  get started in learning calligraphy?‚Äù The answer is simple - just get started! Practice and making mistakes is the best way to develop your own signature style.

One (1) calligraphy brush pen - Ashley's favorite brand!

NATURAL SHAG MOSS is the same as the preserved just NOT dyed. All natural harvested and dried. 2nd photo on the bottom.

Description:
Marimo terrarium... Featured in Nordstom stores. This beautiful glass orb is the perfect terrarium home for these marimo moss balls. The shape magnifies the interior giving you a great view of your little ones!  Measures 3.5" tall x 3" wide".
These sweet little moss balls are ready for adoption. They make the perfect little pets... super quiet and easy to care for and you don't even have to feed them. Legend has it, they will bring you love, happiness and good luck. They're happy floating around in their little aquarium and love to be petted. When they are in a super good mood he will produce little bubbles of oxygen. They would love to keep you company at work.
Japanese marimo moss balls are actually fresh water algae (Cladophora aegagropila). They are soft, fuzzy and super easy to care for. Size will vary, but will average around 1/2" in diameter. Only needs artificial or indirect light and a water change every 1-2 weeks. No direct sun or fertilizer. Marimos can live for several years.
Includes two small Marimo balls (1/2" in diameter), one round glass vase,  sea fan, small shells and your color choice of glass pebbles. 
Please note dimensions before ordering.  Measures 3.5" tall x 3" wide".
Several different colors to choose from. (The color in the photos is crushed shells).
Comes as a easy kit. Just place the pebbles inside the vase, fill with water, and let the little guys go swimming.
Includes detailed assembly and care instructions.
Ships with USPS 2-3 day Priority Mail, tracking and delivery confirmation included.

‚Ä¢ Gold Filled
All gold filled components we use are the highest quality of 14k Gold filled. 14k gold-filled is a solid layer of 14kt gold pressure bonded to a brass base metal. Gold filled jewelry is durable and tarnish resistant, hypoallergenic, and a great quality alternative to solid gold.

925 Sterling silver is an alloy of silver, which consists of 92.5 percent silver and 7.5 percent copper.
It is a timeless and beautiful premium quality metal. A durable option for everyday wear and even if it tarnishes over time, using a polishing cloth will bring back the shine.
‚Ä¢ Gold/Silver Micron Plating
Micron gold plating refers to the depositing at least 1 micron (2-4 Micron in our case) of gold onto a base metal like brass. 
The plate is very reliable and provides a long lasting finish that will last for years.

Product name: Vintage Boys Leather Penny Loafers, Old New Stock, Happy Hikers Boys Shoes Size 2, Happy Hikers Penny Loafers, Vintage Black Penny Loafers,
Description:
a new old stock of boys leather penny loafers that are vintage charming.  the shoes are from the Happy Hikers, a Peters division of International Shoes, St. Louis, MO.
the childrens shoes were a buy out of an old shoe store that had closed and sat uncleaned out.  the shoes are brand new and have never been worn before.  they are in perfect condition and have a perfect throw back charm.  the shoes are a black leather with chunky white stitching  and has the opening for the penny.  the soles are a brown and have a small heel to them.  the shoes have never been worn and the original box is included. the shoe size says size 2-I would believe that this would be a youth size 2.
the original penny loafer years began in the 1930's and were styled after those of Norwegian dairy farmers that had appeared in an article in Esquire Magazine. but the penny didn't enter the equation until John Bass put his own spin on the loafer.  Bass created a slip on shoes that didn't require ties, zippers or buckets.  the decorative strap was designed to look like a pair of lips.  the open area in the strap was soon used to add a decorative element to the shoe such as pennies. when pay-phones were still ubiquitous and hadn‚Äôt yet been raised to a quarter, the penny loafer was often the source of funds for an emergency phone call home, especially for school-age children or teens on dates. 
if you love the vintage lifestyle and enjoy the fashion-how fun is it to bring it to your son! let the vintage lifestyle be a family thing!!!
